Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.37,0:00:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that you left the friends\Nyou traveled together with
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.29,0:00:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all the way from the East Blue, for the ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.92,0:00:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys crying for?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.55,0:00:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You dummy! We're not crying, you dummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.59,0:00:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true that I was moved by your\Nprotecting this ship all by yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.80,0:00:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while all those things were happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.01,0:00:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not crying! None of us are crying!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.60,0:00:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck is their problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.23,0:00:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, now you know that those guys\Nand I are no longer friends, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.28,0:00:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.20,0:00:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll sing about your hardships!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.53,0:00:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The song title is, "Severed Friendship!\NNorthern Wind Chop!"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.74,0:00:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yay! Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.70,0:00:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you making fun of me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.62,0:00:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.38,0:01:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.01,0:01:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll say hello to "Bro" for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.39,0:01:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We now know the location.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.73,0:01:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.80,0:01:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, I made some tea.\NWhy don't you take a break?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.26,0:01:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Oh, thanks. I'll have some\Nonce I finish fixing this spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.07,0:02:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.07,0:02:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.29,0:02:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.62,0:02:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna get to the main issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.71,0:02:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you gonna do after you fix that ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.33,0:02:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.59,0:02:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'll go on an\Nadventure with her again,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.80,0:02:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and someday we'll go back\Nto our home, the East Blue!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.88,0:02:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like we went around the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.30,0:02:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but this is a ship that went to the Grand Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.89,0:02:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be good enough to\Ncall it a triumphant return.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.97,0:02:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hold my head up and--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.43,0:02:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you won't be able to go back...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.65,0:02:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to the East Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.82,0:02:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To begin with, it's too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.03,0:02:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.03,0:02:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we pulled up the ship earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.49,0:02:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was observing her very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.66,0:02:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, you bastards! What're you\Ngonna do with the Merry?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.67,0:03:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take off the ropes! Let the ship down!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do something to the Merry,\Nmy 8,000 men will teach you a lesson!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.72,0:03:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you listening, you bikini jerk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.01,0:03:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you underestimate me, you'll regret it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.64,0:03:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Captain Usopp, the king of\Nthe East Blue who is feared by all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.14,0:03:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Shut up.\N--Ow, ow, ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.94,0:03:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't pinch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.52,0:03:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.15,0:03:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.49,0:03:30.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.41,0:03:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That ship is at the end of her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.70,0:03:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The assessment by Galley-La is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.91,0:03:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As someone who's in the demolition business,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.79,0:03:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest you demolish her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.25,0:03:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.46,0:03:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you demolish your ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.92,0:03:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! What're you saying, you jerk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.97,0:03:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! What're you doing?! Stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.06,0:03:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.97,0:04:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just saying I'll help you demolish that ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.14,0:04:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous! I won't allow that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.36,0:04:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Merry is my ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.82,0:04:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...! She's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.07,0:04:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...no longer a ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.53,0:04:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.37,0:04:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.87,0:04:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked you earlier what you were gonna\Ndo after you fixed this ship, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.04,0:04:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you were going to offer your\Nlife to the sea with this ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.46,0:04:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have said anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.05,0:04:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... you said that you wanted to\Ngo back to the East Blue on this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.02,0:04:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm trying to stop you... brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.06,0:04:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ship... can no longer\Neven reach the next shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.90,0:04:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. Ships are born with a promise
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.82,0:04:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to carry you across the sea\Nfrom one shore to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.25,0:05:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, once a ship can\Nno longer carry you to shore...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.13,0:05:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.63,0:05:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.30,0:05:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once she can't carry you to shore...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.55,0:05:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...she's no longer a ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.93,0:05:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.15,0:05:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.82,0:05:40.14,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.16,0:05:43.64,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.66,0:05:46.98,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,As power passes through our clasped hands
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.00,0:05:55.00,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.97,0:06:05.63,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Working together, let's ride the giant waves
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.65,0:06:12.97,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry toward the excitement--\Nthere's the starting signal
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.99,0:06:19.93,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's the time to set sail-- let's raise anchor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.95,0:06:27.06,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut through the rainbow-colored wind\Nand head for a sea of adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.08,0:06:30.44,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a journey fraught with injury
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.46,0:06:34.40,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but what you cherish most will be right there
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.42,0:06:38.37,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you get into a jam
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.39,0:06:41.45,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll always be there to protect you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.47,0:06:45.62,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.64,0:06:49.17,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.19,0:06:52.17,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If a storm hits, let's put\Nour arms around each other
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.19,0:06:56.43,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and gaze at the light beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.45,0:07:00.35,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If we gather up the pieces of our dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.37,0:07:03.68,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll make a map leading to tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.70,0:07:06.64,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.66,0:07:12.44,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,under the same flag-- together, we're one
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.46,0:07:20.46,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,One Piece
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.05,0:07:30.05,B1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,2000)}"The Man Who Is Loved Even\Nby His Ship! Usopp's Tears!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.16,0:07:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard! Move away from Merry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.13,0:07:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.30,0:08:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.68,0:08:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...take a good look at her...\Nwith your own eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.05,0:11:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Merry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.47,0:11:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fix you right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.73,0:11:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fix you right away... I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.98,0:11:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As many times as you need...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.15,0:11:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fix you as many times as you need!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.65,0:11:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As many times as you need!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.28,0:11:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Enough already, Long-nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.62,0:11:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw the bottom of the ship, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.46,0:11:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the broken keel at the root of her,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.58,0:12:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the outer panels are slipping off\Nand the frames are torn, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.59,0:12:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a ship is like that, she'll just fall\Napart from the outside with each wave!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.59,0:12:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, you think a total\Namateur like you can...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.06,0:12:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.10,0:12:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you to tell me anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.77,0:12:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your mouth shut, or I'll\Nbeat you up, you hooligan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.76,0:12:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.80,0:12:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.14,0:12:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.52,0:13:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.69,0:13:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.73,0:13:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.40,0:13:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At heart... I know it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.58,0:13:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.46,0:13:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that Merry is at the end of her life!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.53,0:13:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.03,0:13:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.62,0:14:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard the assessment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.96,0:14:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was convinced that what I saw\Non that day really happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.04,0:14:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I thought I was dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.84,0:14:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought there was no way\Nsomething like that could happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On one foggy night...\Nin a forest under the moonlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.89,0:14:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the strikes of a wooden hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.56,0:14:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound was coming from the ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.15,0:14:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,although no one was supposed\Nto be on her at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.94,0:14:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It came from our ship, which was\Nscarred and washed ashore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.41,0:14:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was very foggy, but I\Ndefinitely saw someone there...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.66,0:14:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...striking a wooden hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.00,0:14:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't figure out who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.17,0:14:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then, when the morning came the next day,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.22,0:14:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the ship was lousily fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.26,0:15:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The completely broken mast\Nwas also fixed as it used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.97,0:15:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the really mysterious thing was that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.69,0:15:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...whoever fixed the Merry\Nknew how she originally looked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.73,0:15:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite the fact that we\Nhad added lots of tweaks,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.49,0:15:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this person put the Merry back\Nto how she used to look!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.28,0:15:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything was a mystery to us, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.45,0:15:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...for some reason, these words\Nremained in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.96,0:15:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even know if this person actually\Nsaid it or I was imagining things...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.30,0:15:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.51,0:15:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll carry you guys for a little bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.26,0:15:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This may sound stupid, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.48,0:15:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I feel that it might've been\Nan incarnation of the Merry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.03,0:16:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet the ship was already at her limits then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.16,0:16:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she might've turned into\Nthat form to let us know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.46,0:16:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard the assessment,\Nthat's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.34,0:16:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think I'm crazy, don't you?\NYou don't have to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.31,0:16:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.52,0:16:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.06,0:16:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This person looked like a sailor\Nholding a wooden hammer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.03,0:16:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...? Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.11,0:16:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.90,0:16:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.57,0:16:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw a Klabautermann.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.12,0:16:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Klabau...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.04,0:16:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klabautermann.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.54,0:16:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's one of the legends known among sailors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.50,0:17:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fairy that dwells only on a ship\Nthat's treated with great care.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.38,0:17:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you could say it's a ship's incarnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.47,0:17:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They carry wooden hammers in their hands
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.22,0:17:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and are dressed in sailor's raincoats.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.81,0:17:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When danger approaches the ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.43,0:17:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they run around inside the ship\Nand let people know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.35,0:17:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is said that they sometimes\Nhelp sailors quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.44,0:17:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to be honest, this is the first time\NI've heard someone say they saw one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.70,0:17:30.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more care the ship receives,\Nthe more it appreciates the sailors.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.04,0:17:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ship probably wanted to somehow\Ncarry you across to the other shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.17,0:17:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was able to encounter a crew\Nthat she wanted to carry so badly
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.71,0:17:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that she'd borrow a human form to appear...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.55,0:17:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet she's been very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.77,0:17:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Merry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.98,0:18:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.19,0:18:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.40,0:18:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...who talked to me then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.87,0:18:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was really you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.62,0:18:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Merry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.34,0:18:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, for Heaven's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.13,0:18:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had a big fight with your friends\Nknowing your ship is at her limits, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.81,0:18:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.94,0:18:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How inept men are!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.15,0:18:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're fools!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.53,0:18:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like someone's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.83,0:18:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Someone's here"? Who else could\Nit be but Zambai and the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.75,0:19:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did they take the trouble\Nof coming from the sea side?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.34,0:19:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... when they usually\Nuse the upper entrance...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.09,0:19:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They might've brought Straw Hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.31,0:19:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot that I sent for Straw Hat\Nand the others with you as bait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.68,0:19:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They won't come. We're no longer friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.35,0:19:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you so, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.90,0:19:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't they coming in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.66,0:19:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay. I'll open the door now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.12,0:19:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay. Geez, stop ringing the bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.13,0:19:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother... Go back to your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.51,0:19:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that now. I fought\Na duel with my captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.97,0:19:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the ship stuff isn't settled yet, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.48,0:20:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean it hasn't been settled?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.02,0:20:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you know that your ship can't\Nsail anymore, it's simple, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.07,0:20:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave her with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.32,0:20:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take care of her in a way\Nthat you'd approve of.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.58,0:20:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I did earlier, too, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.58,0:20:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to destroy the ship thinking\Nthat it would be best for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.58,0:20:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't stick your nose\Ninto things! It's my business!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.21,0:20:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey, I'm trying to solve your problem!\N--Is it Zambai?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.34,0:20:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should appreciate it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.59,0:20:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should appreciate it? Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.81,0:20:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get it?! It's a\Nnuisance for the ship, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.43,0:20:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She loves you guys so much that\Nshe appeared in human form.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.06,0:20:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she sinks in the middle of the sea\Nwhile you guys are on board...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.86,0:20:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! If that happens, even if she dies,\Nshe'll be filled with regret!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.41,0:20:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She won't be able to rest in peace!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.87,0:20:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when your friends are dying,\Ncan you just leave them saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.33,0:21:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Well, I hope you die\Nwithout suffering at least"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.08,0:21:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you put it that way,\Nthat's a whole different discussion!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.71,0:21:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not! It's that kind of matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.88,0:21:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't get it, do you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.01,0:21:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.01,0:21:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mozu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.73,0:21:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiwi!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.27,0:21:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.19,0:21:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me... for interrupting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.61,0:21:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just, these two ladies didn't let us in, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.67,0:21:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The secretary at Galley-La!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.09,0:21:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you bastards doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.74,0:22:19.31,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We had a dream that day
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.33,0:22:24.14,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Our belief in ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.16,0:22:32.16,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,makes us able to cross the wildly surging ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.30,0:22:41.30,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,You're braver and more caring than anyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.85,0:22:50.85,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever depart this ship\Nand live in a different world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.03,0:23:01.03,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, we can all surely smile
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.25,0:23:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Galley-La! What the hell are you bastards...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.38,0:23:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're Government\Nintelligence agents, Cutty Flam.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.63,0:23:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you know that name?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.63,0:23:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been entrusted with something\Nby the legendary shipwright Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.43,0:23:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, could you please hand over your secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.89,0:23:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.15,0:23:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Franky's Past! The Day the Sea Train First Ran"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.69,0:23:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
